The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, October 14, 2002 				 Role to supervise and educate
								Tarun Kumar Ghosh: What is the role of the Bar Council in promoting the interests of advocates and keeping a watch on their conduct?																																																													The law provides that the Bar Council will not directly interfere in the activities of the universities with regard to the syllabus and the mode of teaching. But from the time they enter the colleges, law students come under the direct supervision of the state Bar Council. Not only that, recently the state Bar Council has taken several steps to develop professional qualities of advocates. Seminars are being held in different places. The Council has also started publishing a journal.
